 32. Top 7 different microservices deployment strategies
========================================================================================================
-> Rolling and Blue-Green focus on availability, Canary and A/B focus on risk reduction,
   Feature Toggles focus on control, and Shadow focuses on validation.
   
 1️- Rolling Deployment
-------------------------------------------
   What it is:
       Update instances one by one without downtime.

   How it works
       Old version is replaced gradually

   Traffic keeps flowing

     Pros
       ✅ Zero downtime
       ✅ Simple
       ✅ Default in Kubernetes

     Cons
       ❌ Old & new versions run together (API compatibility needed)

     Best for
       Small, backward-compatible changes                 
                     
 2️- Blue–Green Deployment
--------------------------------------------------------
      What it is:
         Two environments:

             Blue → current live
             Green → new version

      Switch traffic instantly.

      Pros
        ✅ Zero downtime
        ✅ Easy rollback (just switch back)

      Cons
        ❌ Double infrastructure cost

      Best for
        Banking, payments, critical systems    
        
 3️- Canary Deployment 🐤
------------------------------------------------------
     What it is:
         Release to a small % of users first.

      Example

       5% users → new version
       95% → old version

      Pros
         ✅ Very low risk
         ✅ Real user testing

      Cons
        ❌ Traffic routing is complex

      Best for
         Large-scale, user-facing apps (Netflix, Amazon)
               
 4️- Shadow Deployment
------------------------------------------------------------
     What it is:
         New version receives real traffic, but responses are ignored.

     Pros
        ✅ No user impact
        ✅ Excellent for testing performance

     Cons
        ❌ Extra infra
        ❌ Hard to validate business logic

      Best for
         Performance testing
         Validating new algorithms          
 
 5️- Recreate Deployment
--------------------------------------------------------------------
      What it is:
         Stop old version → start new version.

      Pros
        ✅ Very simple
        ✅ No compatibility issues

      Cons
        ❌ Downtime ❌

      Best for
        Non-critical internal services
        Dev / test environments
 
 6️- A/B Testing Deployment
----------------------------------------------------------
   What it is:
      Different users get different versions to compare behavior.

   Example
      Version A → old UI
      Version B → new UI

   Pros
      ✅ Data-driven decisions
      ✅ Product experimentation

   Cons
      ❌ Complex monitoring
      ❌ Needs analytics setup

   Best for
      UX changes
      Feature optimization
 
 7️- Feature Toggle (Feature Flags)
-------------------------------------------------------------------------
     What it is:
        Deploy code but control features via config.

     Pros
       ✅ Instant enable/disable
       ✅ No redeployment
       ✅ Safer releases

     Cons
       ❌ Code complexity if flags not cleaned

     Best for
        Gradual feature rollout
        Emergency kill-switch
 
 
 33. what are some anti pattern in microservice and how do you avoid them ?
 =====================================================================================================
 -> Most microservice anti-patterns come from tight coupling, shared data, and ignoring failure handling
 
  1️- Distributed Monolith ❌ (MOST IMPORTANT)
  -------------------------------------------------------------------
    What it is
        Services are split physically, but:
                Tightly coupled
                Must be deployed together
                Share database or schema
        Symptoms
               One service down → whole system breaks
               Changes require updating multiple services
        How to avoid
              ✅ Proper service boundaries (DDD)
              ✅ Independent deployment pipelines
              ✅ No shared database
 
 2️- Shared Database Anti-Pattern ❌
----------------------------------------------------------------------------
       What it is
           Multiple microservices use the same database.
       Why it’s bad
           Schema change breaks multiple services
           Tight coupling
           No autonomy
       How to avoid
           ✅ Database per service
           ✅ Communicate via APIs or events
           ✅ Use CDC or event streaming (Kafka)
 
 3️- Chatty Services ❌
-------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        What it is
            Too many synchronous calls between services.
        Example
            Service A → B → C → D
        Problems
            High latency
            Cascading failures
        How to avoid
           ✅ Asynchronous messaging (Kafka/RabbitMQ)
 
 4- No Fault Tolerance ❌
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    What it is
           Assuming all services are always up.
    Problems
           Cascading failures
    How to avoid
          ✅ Circuit Breaker (Resilience4j)
 
